<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>I quote:</p>

<p>"As a convienience, you can easily retrieve rows from the table using primary key values with the find() method. This method returns a Zend_Db_Table_Row object if you attempt to find() only one key, or a Zend_Db_Table_Rowset object if you attempt to find() multiple keys."</p>

<p>This no longer appears to be true. 
$userEntry = $this-&gt;dbTable-&gt;find( $id ); 
// update some fields
$userEntry-&gt;save( ); 
dies with the following message:
Fatal error: Call to undefined method Zend_Db_Table_Rowset::save()</p>

<p>I can only assume that the find() method was changed to always return a rowset.</p>

